Package com.support

Class Order

java.lang.Object
com.support.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
Payment, java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
InRestrOrder, OnlineOrder
public abstract class Order
extends java.lang.Object
implements Payment, java.io.Serializable
It is our abstract order class. We will extends it in OnlineOrder and InRestrOrder. It has a static orderID to keep track it and provide it as unique

    • Order

      public Order()
      It is our default constructor. Here, I assume if date is not specified, new Date() gives current date to Order as order date. Also, everytime an order created, I increment my static orderID by one. With this way, I am aiming having unique orderIDs.
